
Exercise 1 :
How to run the program :
1) When the audio.java class is executed a JFileChooser appears which allows the user to browse for any file on the computer, A .Wav File should be chosen and then the user should press open.
2) A GUI window will appear then the user have to press play to run the chosen .WAV audio file.
3) To resume the audio after clicking pause or mute, the user should click on play button.

Libraries Used :
java.awt.event.MouseEvent;
java.awt.event.MouseListener;
java.io.File;

java.io.IOException;


javax.sound.sampled.AudioInputStream;
javax.sound.sampled.AudioSystem;
javax.sound.sampled.BooleanControl;
javax.sound.sampled.Clip;

javax.sound.sampled.Line;


javax.sound.sampled.LineUnavailableException;

javax.sound.sampled.UnsupportedAudioFileException;
javax.swing.JButton;
javax.swing.JFileChooser;
javax.swing.JFrame;
javax.swing.filechooser.FileNameExtensionFilter;

Exercise 2 :
How to run the program :
1) After executing Exercise2.java class, the user should input in the console either 1 to transform from RGB to HSV or 2 to transform from HSV to RGB.
2) Then the user should enter each value for the chosen color format consecutively, ex : if the user typed 1,
Then a message having please enter the value of R will appear, after which the user has to enter value for R,G,B consecutively in the range from [0,255].
3) If the user chose 2, then input values for HSV should be inserted where H has to be from [0,360[ and both S and V have to be in percentage.

Libraries used :
java.io.BufferedReader;
java.io.IOException;
java.io.InputStreamReader;
